quran[13]{c,v,t}:
  19,39,"And warn them of the day of regret when the affair will be decided, and (at present) they are in a state of heedlessness and (therefore) they do not believe"
  19,40,We will inherit the earth and whoever is on it and they will be returned to Us. (R)
  19,41,"And mention in the book (about) Ibrahim, he was certainly a truthful man, a prophet"
  19,42,"When he said to his father, \"O My father! why do you worship that which neither hears nor sees nor does it make you care-free from anything"
  19,43,"O my father! there has come to me of knowledge, (something) which has not come to you. So follow me I will guide you to the balanced path"
  19,44,"O my father! do not worship the devil, the devil is certainly disobedient to the Beneficent (Allah)"
  19,45,"O my father ! I fear that a punishment from the Beneficent (Allah) may afflict you, then you will become a friend of the devil"
  19,46,"He said, \"Do you forsake my gods O Ibrahim. If you do not desist I will definitely stone you, now go away from me for a long time"
  19,47,"He said, \"Peace be on you ! I will seek protective forgiveness of my Fosterer for you, He is certainly Gracious to me"
  19,48,"And I will withdraw from you and that which you pray to besides Allah, and I will pray to my Fosterer, may be that I will not be unsuccessful in my prayer to my Fosterer"
  19,49,"So when he withdrew from them and that which they worshipped besides Allah, We granted to him Ishaq and Yaqub and We made each one of them a prophet"
  19,50,And We granted to them from Our mercy and We assigned to them a high and true renown. (R)
  19,51,"And mention in the book (about) Musa, he was one who was purified and he was a messenger, a prophet"